OL,3,CThunderstorm warning issued as humid
OL,4,Cweather continues
OL,6,FParts of Wales could be hit by
OL,7,Fthunderstorms this week as hot and
OL,8,Fhumid weather continues into Thursday
OL,9,F(1 August) across the country.
OL,11,FThe news comes after Tuesday (30 July)
OL,12,Fwas provisionally the warmest day of
OL,13,Fthe year so far in the UK, with a
OL,14,Ftemperature of 32C recorded at Kew
OL,15,FGardens and Heathrow in England.
OL,17,FTemperatures will remain warm this
OL,18,Fweek, with a high of 28C expected on
OL,19,FThursday, before cooling off slightly
OL,20,Fto mid and low 20s for the end of the
OL,21,Fweek.
